{
  "texts": [
    "Several observations stand out in Fig. 5.",
    "First, with the exception of LLaMA-1 (30b), we see a general trend in other LLMs, in which the accuracy and F1-score of models improves with the size of fine-tuning data.",
    "Second, one of our salient findings in Fig. 5 and Figure S2 centers on the capabilities of FLAN-T5 XL.",
    "Our analysis reveals that, when fine-tuned, FLAN-T5 (XL) matches or even surpasses the zero-shot accuracy and F1-score of ChatGPT across all tasks and datasets, with a singular exception.",
    "It falls short in classifying the Problem-Solution frames in the 2023 tweets.The third, and arguably the most compelling, finding in Fig.5and Fig.S2centers on the differential rates and magnitudes of improvement observed across models during the fine-tuning process."
  ]
}